						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1393 (1472 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>Registers the gift of the village Muḷḷikkuḍi in Mēl-Śeṅgiḷināḍu, a subdivision of Kāṭṭu-nāḍu <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Jayaśiṅgakulakāla-vaḷanāḍu, by <hi rend="bold">Dēvarāya</hi> <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> <hi rend="bold">Tirumalairāya-sāmantaṉār</hi> who bears the epithets <hi rend="italic">Takkārkkuttakkāṉ</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Rāhutta-miṇḍan</hi> for offerings to god during the service named after him. The deatils of date <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1393, Khara, Mīna ba. 1, Uttiram</hi> correspond to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1472, February 25.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
